    "description": "<p>Paladins devote their life to a cause and fight with empowered righteous fury. They emit an aura to protect those who stand with them... and wield weapons with divine power to smite down those who stand against them.</p>\n<p><strong>Source of Power:</strong> Paladins gain their power from their belief and devotion to their cause. A Paladin that grew up in a small forest and fights to protect the last oak tree could gain magical powers from his passion to protect it. A Paladin whose loved ones were slain could gain powers from his hatred and desire for vengeance toward the perpetrators.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Starting Equipment</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>2 Light Weapons, or Heavy Weapons or Shields</li>\n<li>1 Ranged Weapon with 20 Ammo OR 3 Throwing Weapons</li>\n<li>1 set of Novice Light or Heavy Armor</li>\n<li>X or Y &ldquo;Packs&rdquo; (Adventuring Packs Coming Soon)</li>\n</ul>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Paladin Martial Mastery</h2>\n<p><strong>Combat Masteries: </strong>All Weapons, All Armors, and All Shields.&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Maneuvers &amp; Weapon Passives: </strong>You gain access to all Maneuvers and Weapon Style Passives.</p>\n<p><strong>Techniques Known:</strong> You learn a number of Techniques&nbsp;as shown in the Techniques Known column of the Paladin&nbsp;Class Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Stamina Points: </strong>You have a maximum number of Stamina&nbsp;Points as shown in the Stamina Points column of the Paladin&nbsp;Class Table.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Paladin Spellcasting Mastery</h2>\n<p><strong>Combat Masteries:&nbsp;</strong>Spellcasting.</p>\n<p><strong>Spell List:</strong> When you learn a new Spell, you can choose&nbsp;any Spell on the Divine Spell List, but only Spells from&nbsp;the following Schools of Magic: Abjuration, Conjuration,&nbsp;Divination, Enchantment, and Transmutation.</p>\n<p><strong>Alpha Note:</strong> You get access to the &ldquo;Premade List&rdquo; of &ldquo;Holy&nbsp;Restoration&rdquo; and can only choose Spells from that list&nbsp;that are from the above Spell Schools.</p>\n<p><strong>Cantrips Known:</strong> You learn a number of Spells with the&nbsp;Cantrip Spell Tag as shown in the Cantrips Known column of&nbsp;the Paladin Class Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Spells Known: </strong>You learn an additional number of Spells&nbsp;(with or without the Cantrip Spell Tag) as shown in the Spells&nbsp;Known column of the Paladin Class Table.</p>\n<p><strong>Mana Points:</strong> You have a maximum number of Mana Points&nbsp;equal to your Charisma or Intelligence, whichever is higher.&nbsp;Additionally, your maximum increases by an amount as&nbsp;shown in the Mana Points column of the Paladin Class Table.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<h2>Class Table</h2>\n<table style=\"border-width: 2px; border-style: solid;\" border=\"1\"><colgroup><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col><col></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Level&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Bonus HP</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Attribute Points</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Skill Points</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>&nbsp;Stamina&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: rgb(132, 153, 189);\"><strong>&nbsp;Mana&nbsp;</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: rgb(132, 153, 189);\"><strong>&nbsp;Cantrips Known</strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: rgb(132, 153, 189);\"><strong>&nbsp;Spells Known </strong></td>\n<td style=\"text-align: center; border-width: 2px; background-color: #8499bd;\"><strong>Techniques Known</strong></td>\n<